.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH webp-animate 1  "animate " 
.SH NAME
animate \- Assemble still images into an animated WebP (surpasses img2webp/gif2webp)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBanimate\fR <\fB\-o\fR|\fB\-\-output\fR> [\fB\-\-delay\fR] [\fB\-\-loop\fR] [\fB\-\-bgcolor\fR] [\fB\-\-dispose\fR] [\fB\-\-blend\fR] [\fB\-\-lossy\fR] [\fB\-\-canvas\fR] [\fB\-m\fR|\fB\-\-method\fR] [\fB\-\-input\-format\fR] [\fB\-\-optimize\fR] [\fB\-\-mixed\fR] [\fB\-\-min\-size\fR] [\fB\-\-kmax\fR] [\fB\-\-kmin\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIINPUTS\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Assemble still images into an animated WebP (surpasses img2webp/gif2webp).
.PP
Each input (PNG/JPEG/GIF/TIFF/BMP/PPM/PAM) is decoded and added as one frame. `\-\-delay` sets the per\-frame duration (one value for all, or a comma list), `\-\-loop` the loop count, and `\-\-lossy Q` switches from the lossless default. The canvas defaults to the largest frame, or set it with `\-\-canvas WxH`.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-output\fR \fI<OUTPUT>\fR
Output `.webp` file; `\-` writes stdout
.TP
\fB\-\-delay\fR \fI<MS>\fR [default: 100]
Per\-frame delay in ms: one value for every frame, or a comma list (`40,40,80`)
.TP
\fB\-\-loop\fR \fI<N>\fR [default: 0]
Loop count; `0` (the default) loops forever
.TP
\fB\-\-bgcolor\fR \fI<RRGGBBAA>\fR
Advisory background color as `RRGGBBAA` hex (e.g. `ffffffff`)
.TP
\fB\-\-dispose\fR \fI<DISPOSE>\fR [default: keep]
Disposal method applied to every frame
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
keep: Leave the canvas as\-is for the next frame (the default)
.IP \(bu 2
background: Clear the frame\*(Aqs rectangle to transparent before the next frame
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-blend\fR \fI<BLEND>\fR [default: blend]
Blend method applied to every frame
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
blend: Alpha\-blend the frame over the canvas (the default)
.IP \(bu 2
overwrite: Overwrite the frame\*(Aqs rectangle, ignoring what is underneath
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-lossy\fR \fI<Q>\fR
Encode frames lossily (VP8) at this quality 0\-100; the default is lossless
.TP
\fB\-\-canvas\fR \fI<WxH>\fR
Canvas size as `WxH`; defaults to the largest frame
.TP
\fB\-m\fR, \fB\-\-method\fR \fI<METHOD>\fR
Encoder effort [default: auto, or from env/config]
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
auto: Adapt the search depth to the image\*(Aqs content and size (the default)
.IP \(bu 2
fast: Fastest: the shallowest fixed search
.IP \(bu 2
best: Smallest: the deepest fixed search
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-input\-format\fR \fI<INPUT_FORMAT>\fR
Force the input format instead of sniffing each file
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
png: PNG (any color type; normalized to RGBA8)
.IP \(bu 2
ppm: Netpbm binary PPM (`P6`, RGB)
.IP \(bu 2
pam: Netpbm binary PAM (`P7`, RGBA)
.IP \(bu 2
jpeg: JPEG (decoded to RGBA8; needs the `formats` feature)
.IP \(bu 2
gif: GIF (first frame as a still; whole\-file animation is a separate path)
.IP \(bu 2
tiff: TIFF (decoded to RGBA8; needs the `formats` feature)
.IP \(bu 2
bmp: BMP (decoded to RGBA8; needs the `formats` feature)
.IP \(bu 2
raw: Raw row\-major pixels; requires `\-\-width`/`\-\-height`/`\-\-layout`
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-optimize\fR
Inter\-frame optimize: encode each frame as a minimal delta against the canvas.

The optimizer derives each frame\*(Aqs rectangle, blend, and dispose itself so the result composites pixel\-identically to the full\-frame animation, only smaller; `\-\-blend` and `\-\-dispose` are therefore ignored under `\-\-optimize`.
.TP
\fB\-\-mixed\fR
With \-\-optimize: trial each frame lossy and lossless, keep the smaller (gif2webp \-mixed)
.TP
\fB\-\-min\-size\fR
With \-\-optimize: exhaustively search each frame\*(Aqs rect/blend/dispose/codec (gif2webp `\-min_size`)
.TP
\fB\-\-kmax\fR \fI<N>\fR
With \-\-optimize: force a keyframe at least every N frames (gif2webp \-kmax; 0 = only the first)
.TP
\fB\-\-kmin\fR \fI<N>\fR
With \-\-optimize: never place keyframes closer than N frames apart (gif2webp \-kmin)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
<\fIINPUTS\fR>
Still images, one per frame, in display order (PNG/JPEG/GIF/TIFF/BMP/PPM/PAM)
